        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 6:25PM PDT by NWS Spokane WA</headline>
        <description>At 625 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 20
miles northeast of Elk River, or 29 miles south of Wallace, moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of south central
Shoshone County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
